<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: CZECH IPB POSTS H1 CZK 445MLN.</title>
<headline>CZECH IPB POSTS H1 CZK 445MLN.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-07-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The third largest Czech bank, IPB a.s. said on Monday it posted a 445 million crown net profit in the first six months of 1997 versus 830 million in the same period in 1996, to Czech accounting standards.  </p>
<p>Preliminary results for period ending June 30 1997 (in</p>
<p>billions of crowns accrding to Czech accounting standards).</p>
<p>			    H1 1997		H1 1996</p>
<p> AFTER TAX PROFIT	 0.445		  0.830</p>
<p> BASIC CAPITAL	    5.681		  5.681</p>
<p> OWN CAPITAL	     17.040		 16.484</p>
<p> BALANCE SUM	    233.987		225.712</p>
<p> PRIMARY DEPOSITS     133.110		118.160</p>
<p> NON-BANK CREDITS     152.575		137.152</p>
<p>NOTE: IPB also said that its classified loans represented 19.6</p>
<p>percent of the total compared with 20.0 perecent in the first</p>
<p>half of 1996 and that its capital adequacy was 8.23 percent</p>
<p>versus 10.81 perecnt.</p>
<p>IPB added that the figures were compiled using Czech</p>
<p>National Bank methodology.</p>
<p>-- Robin Shepherd, Prague Newsroom, 420-2-2423-0003</p>
